30/12/2008
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- Foreign Minister Skender Hyseni said on Monday (December 29th) he expects many countries will recognise Kosovo's independence "in the first half of 2009".
He also announced Kosovo will open 12 more embassies and two consulates in the new year.
In other news Monday, two ethnic Albanians reportedly injured three members of the Kosovo Police Service in the divided town of Mitrovica.
According to media reports, the officers -- a Serb, an Albanian and a Bosniak -- came under attack as they conducted regular vehicle inspections in the area.
Police arrested the alleged assailants.
(Koha Ditore, Zeri, Kosova Sot, Express - 30/12/08;
KTV, RTK, B92, Beta, Tanjug, Radio Srbija - 29/12/08)
